element.name: Watching the Silver Birds I by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (2.5/1)

long-description.p:
Dublin Airport is Ireland's biggest airport by with annual passengers of around 20 million.
The airport caters for a wide range of operators both long haul european carriers daily services include Aer Lingus, American Airlines, Delta Airlines & Continental Airlines.
Low cost flights from the airport are of course Ryanair which has its own hub.
The airport offers a number of great vantage points for plane spotters this being one of them.

p.font: The Difficulty rating is to reflect that this area has many muggles at all times of the day and night please beaware of this while hunting for the cache.

long-description.p: The cache is a magnetic micro sized container please rehide it carefully to prevent muggles from discovering its location.

2010-03-07T20:00:00Z : Found it by John NW
How long is the Runway!!!!!?????? This was a long long walk from the last cache on the otherside of the runway! The warmth made it fun too - at least I could spot planes, enjoy a walk in the sun and find caches - could the day get any better?!??!?! The cache was in a bit of a rundown area with lots of litter, if you have youngsters beware, trust the co-ordinates as they were bang on for me. TNLN TFTC
